text.paragraph:
Hepatic Impairment
: There is no information regarding the effect of severe hepatic impairment on exposure to trospium chloride extended-release capsules. In a study of patients with mild (Child-Pugh score 5 to 6) and with moderate (Child-Pugh score 7 to 8) hepatic impairment, given 40 mg of immediate-release trospium chloride, mean Cmax increased 12% and 63% respectively, and mean AUC(0-∞
) decreased 5% and 15%, respectively, compared to healthy subjects.
